revision.text:
{{about|the geological feature|the drainage basin|Amazon Basin}} {{Infobox sedimentary basin | name = Amazon Basin | other_name = ''Bacia do Amazonas'' | named_for = [[Amazon River]] | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | pushpin_map = Brazil | pushpin_map_size = | pushpin_map_alt = | pushpin_map_caption = | pushpin_relief = 1 | pushpin_mark = | pushpin_mark_size = | pushpin_label = | pushpin_label_position = | map_image = Amazon Basin2.jpg | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = The basin is located in the center and center-right of the picture | column_image = | column_size = | column_alt = | column_caption = | section_image = | section_size = | section_alt = | section_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|2|29|47|S|57|3|25|W|display:inline,title}} | location = [[South America]] | region = [[North Region, Brazil|North]] | country = {{BRA}} | state = [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]], [[Pará]] | cities = [[Manaus]] | onoffshore = Onshore | boundaries = [[Guiana Shield]], [[Gurupá Arch]]; [[Marajó Basin]], [[Brazilian Shield]], [[Púrus Arch]]; [[Solimões Basin]] | partof = Amazon basins | seas = | rivers = [[Amazon River]] | lakes = | area = {{convert|620000|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}} | basin_type = [[Continent]]al [[rift basin]] | plate = [[South American Plate|South America]] | orogeny = | age = [[Cambrian]]-[[Holocene|recent]] | stratigraphy = | fields = | faults = | footnotes = | embed = }} The '''Amazon Basin''' is a major {{convert|620000|km2|sqmi}} large [[sedimentary basin]] located roughly at the middle and lower course of the [[Amazon River]], south the [[Guiana Shield]] and north of the [[Amazonian Craton|Central Brazilian Shield]]. It is bound to the west by the [[Púrus Arch]], separating the Amazon Basin from the [[Solimões Basin]] and in the east by the [[Gurupá Arch]], separating the basin from the [[Marajó Basin]].<ref name=Ferreira2015_p1>Ferreira et al., 2015, p.1</ref> The basin developed on a [[rift]] that originated possibly about [[Geologic time scale|550 million years ago]] during the [[Cambrian]]. Parts of the rift were reactivated during the opening of the [[South Atlantic]].<ref>{{cite journal |last=Burke |first=Kevin C. |last2=Lytwyn |first2=Jennifer |date=1993 |title=Origin of the Rift Under the Amazon Basin as a Result of Continental Collision During Pan-African Time |url=http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/00206819309465563 |journal=International Geology Review |publisher=Taylor & Francis |volume=35 |issue=10 |pages=881-897 |doi=10.1080/00206819309465563 |access-date=24 November 2015}}</ref>
The basin has an elongated shape with a WSW-ENE orientation. It long axis runs from the vicinity of [[Manaus]] to the area near the confluence of [[Xingu River]] with the Amazon River.
