A '''cnidariologist''' is a [[zoologist]] specializing in [[Cnidaria]], a group of freshwater and marine aquatic animals that include the [[sea anemones]], [[corals]], and [[jellyfish]].
==Examples== * Edward Thomas Browne (1866-1937) * [[Henry Bryant Bigelow]] (1879-1967) * [[Randolph Kirkpatrick]] (1863–1950) * [[Kamakichi Kishinouye]] (1867-1929) * [[Paul Lassenius Kramp]] (1887-1975) * [[Alfred G. Mayer]] (1868-1922)
