{{geology-book-stub}}

The '''Elsasser number''', Λ, is a dimensionless number in [[magnetohydrodynamics]] that represents the ratio of magnetic forces to the Coriolis force.<ref>Encyclopedia of geomagnetism and paleomagnetism, p. 299</ref>

<math>\Lambda = \frac{\sigma B^2}{\rho \Omega}</math>

where σ is the [[Electrical conductivity|conductivity]] of the fluid, ''B'' is the [[magnetic field]], ρ is the density of the fluid, and Ω is the rate of rotation of the body.

