'''Epsilon 15''' (or '''ε15''') is a [[virus]], specifically a [[bacteriophage]], known to infect species of  ''[[Salmonella]]'' [[bacteria]] including ''[[Salmonella anatum]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Cryo-EM density map of Epsilon-15 bacteriophage icosahedral reconstruction from JADAS automatically acquired data at 7.3 Angstrom resolution.|url=http://www.pdbj.org/emnavi/emnavi_detail.php?id=1557|work=EM Navigator|accessdate=18 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Boutin|first=C.|title=Biologists build better software, beat path to viral knowledge|url=http://www.purdue.edu/uns/html4ever/2006/060201.Jiang.salmonella.html|publisher=Purdue University|accessdate=18 November 2012|date=1 February 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bacteriophage Ecology Group Reference Abstracts |url=http://www.mansfield.ohio-state.edu/~sabedon/ab1980.htm |publisher=Stephen T. Abedon |accessdate=18 November 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101223062418/http://www.mansfield.ohio-state.edu/~sabedon/ab1980.htm |archivedate=23 December 2010 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |pmid=2317154 |year=1990 |last1=Sechter |first1=I |last2=Sechter-Mooreville |first2=R |title=Host-range modifications of bacteriophage epsilon 15 |volume=110 |issue=3–4 |pages=255–7 |journal=Archives of Virology |doi=10.1007/BF01311293}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1038/nature06665 |title=Backbone structure of the infectious ε15 virus capsid revealed by electron cryomicroscopy |year=2008 |last1=Jiang |first1=Wen |last2=Baker |first2=Matthew L. |last3=Jakana |first3=Joanita |last4=Weigele |first4=Peter R. |last5=King |first5=Jonathan |last6=Chiu |first6=Wah |journal=Nature |volume=451 |issue=7182 |pages=1130–4 |pmid=18305544}}</ref>

The virus is a short, tailed phage with a double-stranded DNA [[genome]] of 39,671 [[base pair]]s and 49 [[open reading frame]]s.<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1038/nature04487 |title=Structure of epsilon15 bacteriophage reveals genome organization and DNA packaging/injection apparatus |year=2006 |last1=Jiang |first1=Wen |last2=Chang |first2=Juan |last3=Jakana |first3=Joanita |last4=Weigele |first4=Peter |last5=King|first5=Jonathan |last6=Chiu |first6=Wah |journal=Nature |volume=439 |issue=7076 |pages=612–6 |pmid=16452981 |pmc=1559657}}</ref>

