A '''state mammal''' is the official [[mammal]] of a [[U.S. state]] as designated by a state's legislature. Many states also have separately officially designated [[List of U.S. state animals|state animals]], [[List of U.S. state birds|state bird]]s, [[state fish]], [[state butterfly|state butterflies]], and [[list of U.S. state reptiles|state reptiles]]. States similarly have [[List of U.S. state flowers|state flower]]s, [[List of U.S. state trees|state tree]]s and [[state song]]s.
